truments, we were plugging in a lot, and we started to mess around with feedback and distortion. When you’re on tour you start to mess around a bit more with the live side of things. There were a lot of bands around that were part of the grunge thing, and this wasn’t grunge, but the timing was good. We couldn’t have really fitted in with grunge, because we were just a different type of a band. We were Irish and from Limerick, and we had a lot of our own ideas. A lot of the grunge bands were very similar to each other.  Is there a live performance video for this song?  Genius Answer 2 contributors Yes! The Cranberries performed “Zombie” at NPR’s Tiny Desk Concert.       Is there another live video performance of this song?  What happened to the band now that Dolores has died  Who produced “Zombie” by The Cranberries?  When did The Cranberries release “Zombie”?  Who wrote “Zombie” by The Cranberries?     Stars: The Best of 1992-2002    (2002) The Cranberries 1. Dreams 2. Linger 3. Zombie 4. Ode to My Family 5. I Can’t Be With You 6. Ridiculous Thoughts 7. Salvation 8. Free to Decide 9. When You’re Gone 10. Hollywood 11. Promises 12. Animal Instinct 13. Just My Imagination 14. You and Me 15. Analyse 16. Time Is Ticking Out 17. This Is the Day 18. Daffodil Lament 19. New New York 20. Stars Expand      Credits Producers Julie Gardner & Stephen Street Writer Dolores O’Riordan Bass Guitar Mike Hogan Electric Guitar Noel Hogan & Dolores O’Riordan Video Director Samuel Bayer Vocals Dolores O’Riordan Label Def Jam Recordings Drums Fergal Lawler Recorded At Windmill Lane Studios (Dublin, Ireland) Release Date September 14, 1994 Zombie Samples Odysee auf UKW by J.B.O. (DEU) , Zombie - ambient vocal edit by Elena (Pop) & В мониторе зомби (Zombie In monitor) by Аскар Бракша (Askar Braksha) Songs That Sample Zombie Claws by Kim Petras , DREAMING by Black Dresses , Michael Jackson Has A Weird Fetish (The Rapper Is Here) by DxBoon (Ft. Poppa P.) , Partii by Myth City , Feelings Show